# Google Ads provider

## Tool naming

All tools prefixed `google_`. **14 tools** registered in `tools.go`; implement in:

- `accounts.go` — account discovery
- `reports.go`, `report_search.go`, `report_queries.go`, `reports_legacy.go` — curated reports
- `search_response.go` — empty-result hints + channel sniff
- `google_search_pagination.go` — auto-pagination (`auto_paginate`, default true)
- `google_observability.go` — span attributes + failure logs
- `field_service.go` — `google_get_resource_metadata`
- `generic_search.go` — `google_search_gaql`

## Gateway proxy

Use `proxy.go` / `googleGateway.requestJSON` — never call Google Ads directly. All requests go through mcp-ads-manager with the user's OAuth token and `developer-token` header (gateway adapter).

## MCC / login-customer-id

- `customer_id`: account being queried (client or standalone).
- `login_customer_id`: manager (MCC) id when querying a client under an MCC.
- `google_resolve_customer` returns both when match is under a manager.

## GAQL (curated + hybrid)

- Shared builders: `gaql.go`, `report_queries.go`.
- Validation + allowlist: `gaql_validate.go`, embedded `gaql_resources.txt`.
- Attributed prefixes allowed: `campaign`, `ad_group`, `customer`, `ad_group_ad`, `asset_group` (not a full compatibility matrix).
- Date filters: `segments.date` with `YYYY-MM-DD`.
- Enum filters: uppercase unquoted (`ENABLED`).
- Report limits: default 500, max 1000 per page; `change_event` max 10000; auto-paginate up to 10 pages.
- Field metadata: `POST {version}/googleAdsFields:search` (no customer id).

## Search term tools

| User ask | Tool | Resource |
|----------|------|----------|
| Search campaign queries | `google_search_search_terms` | `search_term_view` |
| Performance Max queries | `google_search_pmax_search_terms` | `campaign_search_term_view` |

Empty Search reports return `hint` + `channel_summary`.

## Hybrid agent workflow

1. Prefer curated tools for common reports.
2. When no curated tool fits: `google_get_resource_metadata` → `google_search_gaql`.
3. Never guess GAQL fields.

